race.comment: COOL STORM (10) progressed nicely last time out to finish a narrow third over 1200m at Newcastle after being prominent at the turn. Tackling a more suitable race from the low gate. Goes close. SARATOGA POWER (8) is in top form with two wins on end, the most recent a slick victory over 900m at Muswellbrook. Mitchell Bell retains the ride and capable of making it three straight wins. DANCES WITH HOOVES (4) beaten for early speed on resumption before surging late for a game second over 1100m at Dubbo. Gets the right tempo to take a hand in the finish. PUERTO BANUS (6) chipped away late on resumption when fifth over 1280m at Muswellbrook in the Denman Cup. Proven second up and deserves consideration.
